I think one of the things that really helped me with that is like in my individual contributor

00:43:10.879 --> 00:43:18.479
role, there were certain projects that I was wholly responsible for already. And so I knew

00:43:18.479 --> 00:43:23.280
a little bit about managing that project, what was involved in terms of talking to the people.

00:43:23.280 --> 00:43:30.080
So I was already doing that for myself. And then as I got promoted in my pipeline, I actually had

00:43:30.080 --> 00:43:39.120
a really great leadership mentor talking me through how he was managing his team, setting

00:43:39.120 --> 00:43:43.679
me up with like, okay, now that you're taking over this responsibility, these are my primary

00:43:43.679 --> 00:43:50.560
contacts. So somebody really set me up for success in that transition into the people

00:43:50.560 --> 00:43:57.840
leadership. Something that I've had to balance with myself is part of that of like, there are

00:43:57.840 --> 00:44:04.239
certain things that I am very good at and I have a lot of experience with within Centene. But now

00:44:05.120 --> 00:44:10.320
if I choose to spend my time doing that, that's time that I'm taking away from something else.

00:44:10.320 --> 00:44:17.520
So balancing that, like I do need to train people to do this task because that's no longer my primary

00:44:17.520 --> 00:44:23.280
responsibility is something that I've been navigating and trying to get better at, especially

00:44:23.280 --> 00:44:27.439
during times when it's not like, hey, we need to turn this around in three hours. Because like,

00:44:27.439 --> 00:44:33.280
if that's the deadline, I'm going to do it. But if we have 24 hours or even three weeks,

00:44:33.439 --> 00:44:38.320
that's something that I can spend the time teaching someone how to do it right

00:44:38.320 --> 00:44:41.600
once and then facilitating that in the future.

