00:44:55.439 --> 00:45:04.479
I don't think so. I think it was just something that like, my reporting chain was generally very

00:45:04.479 --> 00:45:10.239
supportive of moving any people through the career direction that they want to go. And so as I went

00:45:10.239 --> 00:45:15.840
from data scientist one to data scientist two, and my responsibilities grew, and I was feeling

00:45:15.840 --> 00:45:21.919
comfortable, it was a like, hey, do you think you're ready for this? And I said, sure. And then

00:45:22.719 --> 00:45:27.679
once you say sure that you're ready for it, you're going to have to be because now you're doing it.

00:45:28.239 --> 00:45:36.159
And there's no room to be like, oh, just kidding. Let me, you know, please unpromote me. So yeah,

00:45:36.159 --> 00:45:42.000
like, yeah, you, I felt like I was ready. And then as I made that transition, like my reporting

00:45:42.000 --> 00:45:47.600
chain was still intact. And so I still had that support from the top down to help me as I learned

00:45:48.080 --> 00:45:52.719
how to support the people that now report to me.

00:45:55.439 --> 00:46:02.800
Something that's been hard for me is like when that career track doesn't already exist for

00:46:03.439 --> 00:46:11.919
your role, like figuring out how to then go from individual contributor to a manager. And if it's

00:46:11.919 --> 00:46:17.439
like creating your own role or finding a different part within the organization where that would

00:46:17.439 --> 00:46:25.840
fit in as well. Yeah, so I think that's something we've kind of worked with our HR partners,

00:46:26.879 --> 00:46:33.760
being embedded in the actuarial department. I think before I was hired in as a data scientist,

00:46:33.760 --> 00:46:40.080
everyone in that work had to have actuarial titles, even though these were people not pursuing

00:46:40.080 --> 00:46:47.040
actuarial credentials or anything like that. So there was a big push to say like, okay, we're

00:46:47.040 --> 00:46:54.239
actually allowed to hire people with data titles into this role. So there's, it can feel like

00:46:54.239 --> 00:46:59.520
there's a lot of like swimming upstream there because there is corporate inertia for it.

00:46:59.520 --> 00:47:06.639
There's a reason that these orgs were built this way when it started, but having someone

00:47:06.639 --> 00:47:11.679
